<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,222,643]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Of the eight species traditionally listed as inhabiting 
<collectingCountry box="[752,823,223,246]" name="South Korea" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Korea</collectingCountry>
, we regarded 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hoffmann &amp; Lunde" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[982,1102,223,246]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="araneus">
<emphasis box="[982,1102,223,246]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">S. araneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ohdachi &amp; Han" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[1158,1333,222,247]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="unguiculatus">
<emphasis box="[1158,1333,222,247]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">S. unguiculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as either misidentification or error of records. Therefore, we identified six species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Fischer" authorityYear="1814" box="[1002,1064,259,282]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1002,1064,259,282]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Sorex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1100,1172,259,282]" name="South Korea" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Korea</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,222,643]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hoffmann &amp; Lunde" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[199,360,295,318]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="araneus">
<emphasis box="[199,360,295,318]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Sorex araneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a wide distribution in the Palearctic, occurring from Britain through central, northern and eastern Europe and Asia as far east as Lake Baikal and as far north as the Arctic Coast. Since 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Turov" authorityYear="1924" box="[1237,1384,330,355]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="isodon">
<emphasis box="[1237,1384,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Sorex isodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was regarded as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hoffmann &amp; Lunde 2008)" baseAuthorityName="Hoffmann &amp; Lunde" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[292,864,366,391]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="araneus" subSpecies="isodon">
<emphasis box="[292,540,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Sorex araneus isodon</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hoffmann &amp; Lunde" box="[556,856,366,391]" firstAuthor="Hoffmann" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="297 - 327" refId="ref103097" refString="Hoffmann, R. S. &amp; Lunde, D. (2008) Order Soricomorpha-shrews and moles. In: Smith A. T. &amp; Yan, X. (Eds.), A guide to the mammals of China. Princeton University Press, Princeton, pp. 297 - 327." type="book chapter" year="2008">Hoffmann &amp; Lunde 2008</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hoffmann &amp; Lunde" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[878,999,367,390]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="araneus">
<emphasis box="[878,999,367,390]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">S. araneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been listed as a Korean mammal (
<bibRefCitation author="Tate" box="[158,279,403,427]" firstAuthor="Tate" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refId="ref122298" refString="Tate, G. H. (1947) Mammals of Eastern Asia. The Macmillan Company, New York, 366 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 6397" type="book" year="1947">Tate 1947</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Won &amp; Smith" box="[296,534,402,427]" firstAuthor="Won" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="3 - 33" refId="ref125289" refString="Won, C. M. &amp; Smith, K. G. (1999) History and current status of mammals of the Korean Peninsula. Mammal Review, 29, 3 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1365 - 2907.1999.00034. x" type="journal article" year="1999">Won &amp; Smith 1999</bibRefCitation>
). However, the distribution of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hoffmann &amp; Lunde" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[903,1026,403,427]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="araneus">
<emphasis box="[903,1026,403,427]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">S. araneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not extend into eastern Asia (
<bibRefCitation author="Hutterer" box="[158,335,438,463]" firstAuthor="Hutterer" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="220 - 311" refId="ref103962" refString="Hutterer, R. (2005 b) Order Soricomorpha. In: Wilson, D. E. &amp; Reeder, D. M. (Eds.), Mammal species of the world: a taxonomic and geographic reference. 3 rd Edition. The Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore, Maryland, pp. 220 - 311." type="book chapter" year="2005" yearSuffix="b">Hutterer 2005b</bibRefCitation>
). Thus, we delisted 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hoffmann &amp; Lunde" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[557,675,439,462]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="araneus">
<emphasis box="[557,675,439,462]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">S. araneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the mammals of 
<collectingCountry box="[932,1004,439,462]" name="South Korea" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Korea</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,222,643]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ohdachi &amp; Han" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[199,413,474,499]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="unguiculatus">
<emphasis box="[199,413,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Sorex unguiculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
share morphological similarities with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Turov" authorityYear="1924" box="[842,945,474,499]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="isodon">
<emphasis box="[842,945,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">S. isodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
such as large body size, dark-brown ventral color, and broad forefeet. The collection of specimens of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ohdachi &amp; Han" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[805,980,510,535]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="unguiculatus">
<emphasis box="[805,980,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">S. unguiculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1017,1160,510,535]" name="North Korea" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">North Korea</collectingCountry>
brings into question the problem of possible misidentification (
<bibRefCitation author="Han" box="[609,806,546,571]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Han" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="141 - 144" refId="ref101952" refString="Han, S. H., Ohdachi, S. &amp; Abe, H. (2000) New records of two Sorex species (Soricidae) from South Korea. Mammal Study, 25, 141 - 144. https: // doi. org / 10.3106 / mammalstudy. 25.141" type="journal article" year="2000">
Han 
<emphasis box="[670,732,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
2000
</bibRefCitation>
). The identification of these specimens is apparently problematic (
<bibRefCitation author="Han" box="[299,474,582,607]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Han" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="141 - 144" refId="ref101952" refString="Han, S. H., Ohdachi, S. &amp; Abe, H. (2000) New records of two Sorex species (Soricidae) from South Korea. Mammal Study, 25, 141 - 144. https: // doi. org / 10.3106 / mammalstudy. 25.141" type="journal article" year="2000">
Han 
<emphasis box="[354,410,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
2000
</bibRefCitation>
) and should be examined to validate their identity. For the moment, we chose to delist 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ohdachi &amp; Han" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[151,324,618,643]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="unguiculatus">
<emphasis box="[151,324,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">S. unguiculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Korean mammals.
</paragraph>
